               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BESLET</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">submitted that the</hi> 13<hi rend="italic">th Section of the Debtors Act, on whidt the prosecution relied, had, not application to a bankrupt, and cited the Queen v. Boyd in support of that contention. He further contended that there me no evidence showing that the transfer of defendant's property wot in any way fraudulent. The</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">held that the words any person"in the</hi> 13<hi rend="italic">th Section were wide enough to include a bankrupt, and that ike evidence as to the fraudulent character of the transfer must go to the Jury.</hi>
